# Plan: Adreno A7XX Support

## Goal

Add support for Adreno A7XX (gen 7) GPUs to the `hardware-perfcounter` library,
following the existing A5XX / A6XX architecture and using the existing
`generate_adreno_definitions.py` script as the data-source pipeline.

## Background

The library currently exposes Adreno GPU performance counters for A5XX and A6XX
only. Mesa/freedreno's `fd7_perfcntr.c` and the
`mesa/src/freedreno/registers/adreno/a7xx_perfcntrs.xml` register database
prove the upstream model already covers A7XX (FD725 / FD730 / FD735 / FD740 /
FD750, Adreno X1-45 / X1-85) with a stable
`<group>_perfcounter_select` enumerable interface that is identical in shape
to A6XX.

The user-mode library talks to the kernel only via
`ADRENO_IOCTL_COUNTER_GET` / `PUT` / `READ` (group_id + countable_selector),
so a7xx hardware differences (e.g. `RBBM_PERFCTR2_*`, `REG6`/`REG7` register
mixing, BV counter selects) are handled entirely inside the KGSL driver. The
library code therefore does not need to change its ioctl surface.

- **Data source for A7XX**: A7XX register XML is **not** present in the
  envytools submodule (verified at commit `d88cafa3` — no `a7xx.xml` in
  `third_party/envytools/registers/adreno/`, and no A7XX-related commits in
  the entire submodule history). The reference data source is mesa's
  `mesa/src/freedreno/registers/adreno/a7xx_perfcntrs.xml`, which uses the
  same `nouveau:` XML namespace. It has been vendored into
  `third_party/envytools/registers/adreno/a7xx.xml`, with a sibling
  `freedreno_copyright.xml` copy so the existing `<import>` directives
  resolve. A live parse of the vendored file yields **18 groups, 966
  countables** (CP 81, RBBM 14, PC 52, VFD 25, HLSQ 58, VPC 44, TSE 20,
  RAS 30, UCHE 59, TP 133, SP 151, RB 54, VSC 5, CCU 23, LRZ 28, CMP 50,
  GBIF 81, UFC 58). The two a7xx-only groups are `GBIF` and `UFC`.

## Key facts from the codebase investigation

- Script: `scripts/generate_adreno_definitions.py` reads two envytools-style
  XML files and produces `a5xx.{h,c}`, `a6xx.{h,c}`, `common.{h,c}`.
- Series detected by `lib/gpu/adreno/context.c::hpc_gpu_adreno_get_series()`:
  - `500–599`  -> `HPC_GPU_ADRENO_SERIES_A5XX`
  - `600–699` + `702` -> `HPC_GPU_ADRENO_SERIES_A6XX`
  - anything else -> `HPC_GPU_ADRENO_SERIES_UNKNOWN`
- Group ID space: 8 bits per group (`ADRENO_MAX_NUM_COUNTER_BIT_PER_GROUP=8`),
  existing IDs span `0x00`–`0x26` (CP .. MHUB), so a7xx-only groups
  (`GBIF`, `UFC`) can be appended with new IDs without collisions.
- A7XX XML naming convention differs from A6XX:
  - A6XX: `name="PERF_CP_ALWAYS_COUNT"`
  - A7XX: `name="A7XX_PERF_CP_ALWAYS_COUNT"`
  The current script strips `PERF_` and the group prefix; on a7xx input the
  resulting symbol would keep a stray `A7XX_` prefix and break the
  group-prefix convention. The script must also strip the leading
  `<series>_` prefix to stay consistent and to keep `get_common_series()`
  symbol-level matching intact. **Verified empirically**: with the current
  script unchanged, the common set across (a5xx, a6xx, a7xx) collapses to
  zero in every shared group because the symbols no longer match
  (`ALWAYS_COUNT` vs `A7XX_ALWAYS_COUNT`). After the prefix fix the common
  set resumes normally.
- A7XX adds two new groups not present in A6XX:
  - `a7xx_gbif_perfcounter_select` (GBIF)
  - `a7xx_ufc_perfcounter_select`  (UFC)
- Kernel ioctl subset in `third_party/linux/adreno_driver_ioctl.h` is
  unchanged for A7XX; the KGSL driver abstracts register layout.

## Changes

### Required

1. `scripts/generate_adreno_definitions.py`
   - Add `--a7xx_xml` CLI argument.
   - In `parse_xml_file`, after stripping `PERF_`, also strip a leading
     `<series>_` prefix so a7xx symbols come out as `CP_ALWAYS_COUNT`
     instead of `A7XX_ALWAYS_COUNT`.
   - Extend `ADRENO_COUNTER_GROUP_IDS` with `GBIF` and `UFC` (new IDs after
     `0x26`, e.g. `0x27`/`0x28`).
   - In `main()`, parse the a7xx XML, write `a7xx.h` and `a7xx.c` via
     `update_generated_file`, and include the a7xx series in
     `AdrenoAllSeriesDefinition` so `get_common_series()` is recomputed
     across `(a5xx, a6xx, a7xx)`.

2. `lib/gpu/adreno/context.h`
   - Add `HPC_GPU_ADRENO_SERIES_A7XX` to `hpc_gpu_adreno_series_t`.

3. `lib/gpu/adreno/context.c`
   - In `hpc_gpu_adreno_get_series()`, add a branch for A7XX
     (e.g. `gpu_id >= 700 && gpu_id < 800`; the existing special-case
     `gpu_id == 702` stays in the A6XX branch because A702 is an A6XX
     derivative).
   - In `hpc_gpu_adreno_context_start_counters` /
     `_stop_counters`, add an `HPC_GPU_ADRENO_SERIES_A7XX` case mirroring
     the A6XX / A5XX branches (the activate/deactivate ioctl is identical
     across all three).

4. `include/hpc/gpu/adreno/a7xx.h` (new)
   - Mirror `a6xx.h`: declare `hpc_gpu_adreno_a7xx_counter_t`, the
     `hpc_gpu_adreno_a7xx_{create,destroy}_{context,start,stop,query}_counters`
     functions, and contain a `BEGIN/END AUTOGENERATED REGION; DO NOT EDIT!`
     marker block where the script writes the enum.

5. `lib/gpu/adreno/a7xx.c` (new)
   - Mirror `a6xx.c`: wrap `hpc_gpu_adreno_{create,destroy}_context`,
     `_start_counters`, `_stop_counters`, `_query_counters`; switch on the
     detected series and reject A5XX with
     `-HPC_GPU_ERROR_INCOMPATIBLE_DEVICE`.

6. `lib/gpu/adreno/CMakeLists.txt`
   - Add an `hpc_cc_library(NAME a7xx ...)` target depending on `::context`
     and installable under component `AdrenoGPU`, mirroring the existing
     `a5xx` / `a6xx` targets.

7. `scripts/CMakeLists.txt`
   - Extend the `add_custom_command` for the Adreno definitions target so it
     also passes `--a7xx_xml`, depends on the a7xx XML path, and produces
     `a7xx.h` / `a7xx.c`.

### Optional / recommended

8. `examples/adreno_a7xx_c_example.c` (new)
   - Mirror `adreno_a6xx_c_example.c` and exercise a small set of A7XX
     counters (e.g. `SP_BUSY_CYCLES`, `SP_VS_INSTRUCTIONS`,
     `SP_FS_INSTRUCTIONS`).

9. `third_party/envytools/registers/adreno/a7xx.xml` (vendored, done)
   - Copied from `mesa/src/freedreno/registers/adreno/a7xx_perfcntrs.xml`
     (59576 bytes, 18 enums, 966 values).
   - Sibling `third_party/envytools/registers/adreno/freedreno_copyright.xml`
     added so the file's `<import>` directive resolves (envytools convention
     keeps copyright under `registers/`, the copy moves it next to
     `adreno/`-level files where the a7xx XML lives).
   - The vendored file is now inside the submodule path but **not** tracked
     by it (it is a regular tracked file in the superproject, not part of
     envytools' own tree). On `git submodule update`, it will be wiped.
     It should be re-copied, or better, placed outside the submodule
     (e.g. `third_party/a7xx_perfcntrs.xml` in the superproject) and
     pointed at by the script. **TODO: relocate before committing**.

10. `README.md`
    - Mention A7XX support in the "Goals and Features" section.

## Out of scope

- Derived counters (mesa `fd7_perfcntr.c` defines 60+ derived metrics such as
  `percent_shaders_busy`, `avg_bytes_per_fragment`, and a per-GPU
  `fd_derivation_context.a7xx.{number_of_usptp, number_of_alus_per_usptp}`).
  These are an independent, larger feature; current `hardware-perfcounter`
  has no derived-counter API.
- Kernel ioctl additions: the existing four `ADRENO_IOCTL_*` are sufficient
  for the user-mode library.
- A8XX: nearby in mesa (`a8xx_enums.xml`, `a8xx_descriptors.xml`), but
  out of scope here. The script change in this plan can be parameterized
  for `--<series>_xml` to ease follow-up.

## Risk / open questions

- **Data source XML format**: confirmed via live parse of the vendored
  file. All 966 value names start with `A7XX_PERF_` (e.g.
  `A7XX_PERF_CP_ALWAYS_COUNT`). The script's prefix-strip fix is
  therefore: after stripping `PERF_`, also strip a leading `<series>_`
  (case-sensitive, e.g. `A7XX_`). This is generic and will work for
  A8XX too if/when that data source arrives.
- **`gpu_id` range for A7XX**: A702 stays in A6XX branch (it is an A6XX
  derivative). Need to confirm the upper bound for A7XX; `FD750` and
  `Adreno X1-85` are 4-digit IDs but still < 1000. Initial assumption:
  `[700, 800)` excluding `702`.
- **`common.h` shrinkage**: a7xx renames or drops some A6XX-only counters
  (e.g. `PC_STALL_CYCLES_TSE_ONLY` vs. `PC_STALL_CYCLES_VFD_ONLY`), so
  symbol-level intersection will remove them from the common set. This is
  expected behavior, not a bug, but should be called out in the commit.
- **A702 stays in A6XX**: do not fold it into the A7XX range.

## Suggested order of implementation

1. ~~Verify A7XX XML source format (mesa vs. envytools).~~ **DONE**: mesa
   format vendored at `third_party/envytools/registers/adreno/a7xx.xml`;
   live-parsed; 18 groups, 966 countables, all named `A7XX_PERF_*`.
2. **Relocate the vendored a7xx XML outside the submodule** so it is
   not wiped by `git submodule update`. Suggested location:
   `third_party/a7xx_perfcntrs.xml` (superproject-tracked) with a
   clear README at `third_party/a7xx_perfcntrs.README.md` explaining
   provenance and upstream sync procedure.
3. Update `generate_adreno_definitions.py` (symbol stripping, group IDs,
   new `--a7xx_xml` arg, common over three series).
4. Add `a7xx.h` and `a7xx.c` shells with the autogen marker.
5. Extend `context.h` / `context.c` with the A7XX series enum and
   detection.
6. Wire `lib/gpu/adreno/CMakeLists.txt` and `scripts/CMakeLists.txt`.
7. Build, run the example.
8. Commit, push, update README.
